    <text>
        <body>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Columbus Ga</placeName>
                <date>Sept 8th 1867</date>
            </p>
            <p>Rev Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Your esteemed note enclosed<lb/> in the package of Books was duly
                received<lb/> allow me to thank you for myself &amp; wife<lb/> for your kind
                greetings &amp; <sic>wel</sic> wishes and<lb/> I trust the day may not be far
                distant when<lb/> we will become acquainted with each other<lb/> “a la personel”</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Enclosed I hand you a post office<lb/> draft for the prayer Books
                &amp; Almanacs say<lb/> $7.75 the other Books I am sorry to<lb/> say I had to turn
                over to <persName>I. I. Moses<lb/> Esq.</persName> agreeable to your direction as I
                did<lb/> purchase copies of all three of those of <persName>Miss<lb/> Bloch &amp;
                    Co.</persName> of <placeName>Cincinnati</placeName></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">My wife unites with me in wishing<lb/> you many happy years and begs
                me to<lb/> remember her kindly to you.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I am Rev Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">very Respectfully</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">
                <persName role="author">Samuel Meyer</persName>
            </p>
        </body>
    </text>
